                    </div>
        <h2>
            <a href="/articles/analysis/superplatform-framework">
                
<span>Superplatform: A framework to analyse and regulate Google’s online ad ecosystem</span>

                            </a>
        </h2>
        <div class="meta">
            <a href="/users/koray-caliskan" hreflang="en">Koray Caliskan</a>, <em>Parsons School of Design</em><br/><a href="/users/donald-mackenzie" hreflang="en">Donald MacKenzie</a>, <em>University of Edinburgh</em><br/><a href="/users/addie-mcgowan" hreflang="en">Addie McGowan</a>, <em>University of Salford</em><br/>
            PUBLISHED ON:&nbsp;<span class="meta__date">18 Feb 2026</span>
                DOI:&nbsp;<span style="color:#3d3f41;">10.14763/2026.1.2077</span>

        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="content">
          <p>The concept of the "superplatform" presents a simple way to describe Google’s vast and complex online ad business as a dual-core system that merges market power, infrastructural dominance, and supply chain demarketisation.</p>



    </div>
